            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "#35002 involves moving the local variable `all_clients` to `lsp.client._all`. Before that change, this spot used `all_clients`, so it’s simply being replaced with `lsp.client._all`, without any change in logic.\r\n\r\nNote that the `get_clients` used to create `active_clients` returns a copy of `client._all`. The stop operation executed here mutates `client._all, but `active_clients` does not change. So it’s indeed possible this was intentional, though I don’t know the reason.",
